541
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:12,200
It's not heavy.

542
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,960
Shuai is a dummy except for his arithmetic skills,

543
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:14,760
he won't make it

544
00:21:14,760 --> 00:21:15,980
if he gets exiled 3,000 li away!

545
00:21:16,570 --> 00:21:17,790
Mr. Cheng.

546
00:21:17,790 --> 00:21:18,630
I beg of you.

547
00:21:18,630 --> 00:21:19,170
Find a way

548
00:21:19,170 --> 00:21:20,350
to clear his name.

549
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:21,310
It's easy.

550
00:21:21,940 --> 00:21:23,830
Take your confession and tear it up.

551
00:21:23,830 --> 00:21:25,350
Turn yourself in at the government office,

552
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:26,520
and tell them

553
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:27,700
you were behind the whole thing.

554
00:21:28,330 --> 00:21:29,760
He'll be fine then.

555
00:21:48,950 --> 00:21:49,750
Wait.

556
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:56,220
Shuai Jiamo's sentence

557
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:58,110
depends on Prefect Huang.

558
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,010
I'll be off now.

559
00:22:03,150 --> 00:22:05,120
[Prison]

560
00:22:05,670 --> 00:22:06,800
Guards!

561
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:08,230
Help!

562
00:22:08,230 --> 00:22:09,650
-Come here. -What are you doing?

563
00:22:09,650 --> 00:22:10,580
Help! Help!

564
00:22:10,580 --> 00:22:11,670
Why aren't you sleeping?

565
00:22:11,670 --> 00:22:13,010
We need to change cells.

566
00:22:13,350 --> 00:22:14,740
What's wrong with you?

567
00:22:15,580 --> 00:22:16,960
Changing cells in the middle of the night.

568
00:22:17,130 --> 00:22:18,140
This- This cell...

569
00:22:18,350 --> 00:22:19,940
I- can't stay here anymore.

570
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:21,370
The new guy...

571
00:22:21,540 --> 00:22:22,420
So what if he's new?

572
00:22:22,720 --> 00:22:23,770
Is he sick

573
00:22:24,310 --> 00:22:25,490
or did he see a ghost?

574
00:22:25,660 --> 00:22:27,500
We wanted to intimidate him.

575
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:28,130
But he...

576
00:22:28,130 --> 00:22:29,390
He...

577
00:22:38,050 --> 00:22:39,980
He kept mumbling

578
00:22:39,980 --> 00:22:42,200
and even drew sigils on the ground.

579
00:22:42,620 --> 00:22:44,640
And I saw

580
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:45,560
a wisp of black smoke

581
00:22:45,860 --> 00:22:47,330
floating in through that window

582
00:22:47,330 --> 00:22:48,290
with my own eyes.

583
00:22:52,280 --> 00:22:53,460
Could he be

584
00:22:54,340 --> 00:22:55,220
possessed?

585
00:22:55,220 --> 00:22:56,270
It's possible!

586
00:22:56,270 --> 00:22:57,030
I can't live here anymore,

587
00:22:57,030 --> 00:22:57,870
it's too scary.

588
00:22:57,870 --> 00:22:58,420
Yes.

589
00:22:58,420 --> 00:23:00,430
I'll confess everything I did.

590
00:23:00,430 --> 00:23:02,030
Let us go somewhere else.

591
00:23:03,710 --> 00:23:04,460
Hurry up.

592
00:23:04,630 --> 00:23:05,510
Open the door.

593
00:23:05,510 --> 00:23:06,770
Come on.

594
00:23:06,770 --> 00:23:07,240
Here.

595
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:08,160
Wait.

596
00:23:08,830 --> 00:23:10,390
-Let's go. -Look at this.

597
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:24,880
Ghost!

598
00:23:33,740 --> 00:23:34,410
Master Fan.

599
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,300
Fortunately, I did not let you down.

600
00:23:46,630 --> 00:23:48,440
Alright. You may go.

601
00:23:51,960 --> 00:23:53,560
Magistrate Deng, Old Mister Ren,

602
00:23:53,730 --> 00:23:55,030
farewell.

603
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:56,670
-See you. -See you.

604
00:24:19,730 --> 00:24:20,520
Looks like

605
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:22,200
you have a trump card.

606
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:24,300
Hurry up.

607
00:24:24,510 --> 00:24:25,730
You're too slow.

608
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:27,120
I'll hurry.

609
00:24:48,580 --> 00:24:50,470
[Renhua]

610
00:24:51,020 --> 00:24:51,860
It's fresh out of the oven.

611
00:25:02,270 --> 00:25:03,780
You scared me!

612
00:25:04,410 --> 00:25:05,460
Don't say that.

613
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:06,770
We saw a spirit

614
00:25:07,230 --> 00:25:08,110
last night.

615
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:09,030
Spirit?

616
00:25:09,580 --> 00:25:11,010
There are spirits

617
00:25:11,180 --> 00:25:12,810
in a prison as lame as this?

618
00:25:12,810 --> 00:25:13,360
Keep your voice down.

619
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:14,240
Yes.

620
00:25:14,450 --> 00:25:15,540
There really was a cat spirit.

621
00:25:15,540 --> 00:25:17,100
We saw it last night.

622
00:25:17,640 --> 00:25:18,570
I think

623
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:21,420
the cat spirit that eats straw mats

624
00:25:21,420 --> 00:25:22,050
possessed him.

625
00:25:22,350 --> 00:25:22,980
Possessed who?

626
00:25:23,190 --> 00:25:24,110
The one from yesterday.

627
00:25:24,110 --> 00:25:24,990
He-

628
00:25:25,120 --> 00:25:26,500
The one who just came in yesterday.

629
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:27,810
He's called...

630
00:25:28,140 --> 00:25:29,110
Shuai Jiamo.

631
00:25:29,610 --> 00:25:30,120
Him?

632
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:34,650
This is the prison.

633
00:25:34,780 --> 00:25:35,620
What are you doing here?

634
00:25:36,750 --> 00:25:37,630
Greetings, Sirs.

635
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:39,150
I want to visit someone.

636
00:25:39,270 --> 00:25:40,870
Do you have a document from the Office of Justice

637
00:25:40,870 --> 00:25:43,510
or a letter from the Prefect?

638
00:25:58,420 --> 00:25:59,310
Who are you visiting?

639
00:25:59,470 --> 00:26:01,150
Shuai Jiamo. He just came yesterday.

640
00:26:05,940 --> 00:26:06,660
Tell him

641
00:26:06,660 --> 00:26:07,790
the two of us

642
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:09,680
are on orders to stand guard here.

643
00:26:09,930 --> 00:26:11,320
We have no grudge against him.

644
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:12,490
Tell him to spare us

645
00:26:12,490 --> 00:26:13,800
from his hoodoo.

646
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:15,850
Please come in.

647
00:26:17,110 --> 00:26:18,500
Yes, this way.

648
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:24,630
Shuai.

649
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:26,440
Are you okay?

650
00:26:27,070 --> 00:26:27,870
You came at the right time.

651
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:28,790
I found

652
00:26:28,790 --> 00:26:30,180
a new way to prove it—

653
00:26:30,180 --> 00:26:31,060
That's not important anymore.

654
00:26:31,060 --> 00:26:31,940
Why not?

655
00:26:32,230 --> 00:26:33,330
I found a new way

656
00:26:33,330 --> 00:26:34,500
to prove the relationship

657
00:26:34,500 --> 00:26:35,090
between the Silk Poll Tax

658
00:26:35,090 --> 00:26:35,970
and the provisions supplement.

659
00:26:35,970 --> 00:26:37,480
As long as I get the original registers,

660
00:26:37,650 --> 00:26:38,530
I can calculate it.

661
00:26:38,530 --> 00:26:39,500
Shuai!

662
00:26:43,070 --> 00:26:43,830
I have to get something clear

663
00:26:43,830 --> 00:26:44,710
today

664
00:26:45,760 --> 00:26:46,430
because it concerns

665
00:26:46,430 --> 00:26:47,690
many important things.

666
00:26:48,020 --> 00:26:48,700
Go ahead.

667
00:26:51,800 --> 00:26:52,600
Was

668
00:26:56,170 --> 00:26:57,680
what Cheng Renqing said yesterday

669
00:26:58,690 --> 00:27:00,250
true?

670
00:27:05,540 --> 00:27:06,380
What?

671
00:27:07,340 --> 00:27:08,060
He said

672
00:27:08,060 --> 00:27:09,150
you're making use of the Silk Poll Tax

673
00:27:09,280 --> 00:27:10,410
to cause trouble in Jin'an Prefecture

674
00:27:10,410 --> 00:27:11,290
in order to avenge your parents.

675
00:27:11,290 --> 00:27:12,680
Is that true?

676
00:27:20,280 --> 00:27:20,870
No.

677
00:27:23,720 --> 00:27:24,900
I can't remember anything

678
00:27:27,420 --> 00:27:29,020
about my parents.

679
00:27:33,510 --> 00:27:35,060
I know you don't lie.

680
00:27:35,060 --> 00:27:36,070
But after listening to

681
00:27:36,070 --> 00:27:37,160
Cheng Renqing's story,

682
00:27:37,330 --> 00:27:38,380
you responded really strangely

683
00:27:38,380 --> 00:27:39,100
and then passed out.

684
00:27:39,100 --> 00:27:40,020
I've never seen that from you before!

685
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:46,110
I had a splitting headache.

686
00:27:48,550 --> 00:27:49,720
Many things from the past

687
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:52,580
swept into my mind

688
00:27:52,910 --> 00:27:54,260
like a gust of wind.

689
00:27:55,900 --> 00:27:57,240
But they were all jumbled up.

690
00:27:59,420 --> 00:28:00,600
I couldn't tell

691
00:28:01,820 --> 00:28:03,250
which ones were real

692
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:05,930
and which ones were fake.

693
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:12,700
Did you really

694
00:28:14,250 --> 00:28:14,880
have no memory of them

695
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:16,100
before this?

696
00:28:35,500 --> 00:28:37,180
I wish I could remember.

697
00:28:38,480 --> 00:28:40,290
But I can't even remember

698
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:43,020
what my parents looked like.

699
00:28:46,550 --> 00:28:47,510
In the past,

700
00:28:48,230 --> 00:28:49,400
even if someone scolded me,

701
00:28:50,120 --> 00:28:51,420
saying my father did something wrong,

702
00:28:52,510 --> 00:28:53,850
I could never get angry.

703
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:56,210
Because I didn't know

704
00:28:56,210 --> 00:28:57,260
what he did.

705
00:29:00,620 --> 00:29:02,210
But you remember

706
00:29:02,630 --> 00:29:04,140
the arithmetic your father taught you.

707
00:29:07,290 --> 00:29:08,300
Because arithmetic

708
00:29:08,810 --> 00:29:10,020
is the only thing

709
00:29:10,190 --> 00:29:11,620
I care about in this world.

710
00:29:15,440 --> 00:29:16,660
You don't understand.

711
00:29:17,880 --> 00:29:19,560
It's like how I could never understand

712
00:29:19,730 --> 00:29:20,940
why you think

713
00:29:20,940 --> 00:29:22,080
brothels and gambling houses

714
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:23,380
are so fun.

715
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:24,980
You will also never understand

716
00:29:25,350 --> 00:29:27,710
how interesting arithmetic is.

717
00:29:32,280 --> 00:29:33,210
Interesting?

718
00:29:35,900 --> 00:29:36,990
Numbers are simple by nature.

719
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:38,630
Arithmetic is the most honest thing

720
00:29:38,630 --> 00:29:39,630
in the world.

721
00:29:40,260 --> 00:29:41,610
One plus one is always two.

722
00:29:41,610 --> 00:29:43,200
Five times four is always twenty.

723
00:29:43,200 --> 00:29:44,090
And the square of 12

724
00:29:44,090 --> 00:29:46,020
is always 144.

725
00:29:56,180 --> 00:29:57,610
People are unpredictable and hard to figure out,

726
00:29:57,780 --> 00:29:59,500
but numbers are simple and never deceive us.

727
00:29:59,500 --> 00:30:00,590
The relationships between numbers

728
00:30:00,590 --> 00:30:02,400
are like the constellations in the sky,

729
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:03,490
they don't ever change.

730
00:30:06,430 --> 00:30:07,600
As long as you understand

731
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:09,160
the principles of their workings and the methods of calculation,

732
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:10,210
you can find out

733
00:30:10,210 --> 00:30:11,170
anything you wish to know!

734
00:30:11,300 --> 00:30:13,480
This is what I pursue!

735
00:30:13,480 --> 00:30:15,040
Even if there are infinitely many numbers,

736
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:16,630
even if the sums are complex,

737
00:30:16,630 --> 00:30:19,700
fundamental principles allow me to command them!

738
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:21,210
Perhaps to you,

739
00:30:21,340 --> 00:30:22,260
this is just

740
00:30:22,260 --> 00:30:23,730
a room filled with

741
00:30:23,730 --> 00:30:24,610
tattered official newspapers.

742
00:30:24,610 --> 00:30:25,620
But to me,

743
00:30:25,620 --> 00:30:27,390
this is the way to the abode of the Immortals!

744
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:29,570
Here, my spirit wanders

745
00:30:29,570 --> 00:30:31,040
up into the heavens and down into the netherworld!

746
00:30:31,040 --> 00:30:31,710
Countless sceneries appear

747
00:30:31,710 --> 00:30:32,590
in a blink of an eye!

748
00:30:32,590 --> 00:30:33,810
What is this, if not true freedom?

749
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:04,350
What's the difference between this

750
00:31:06,280 --> 00:31:07,920
and becoming an Immortal?

751
00:31:16,150 --> 00:31:19,970
[3,530]

752
00:31:36,260 --> 00:31:38,450
Well said...

753
00:31:39,580 --> 00:31:41,470
What- What does that mean?

754
00:31:44,120 --> 00:31:44,960
I didn't understand either.

755
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:47,230
But it doesn't matter anymore.

756
00:31:48,700 --> 00:31:49,370
Shuai,

757
00:31:49,750 --> 00:31:50,960
wait for me here.

758
00:32:04,870 --> 00:32:06,250
It's time to change the straw mat.

759
00:32:07,010 --> 00:32:07,850
We'll change it.

760
00:32:07,850 --> 00:32:09,070
-Right away. -Right now.

761
00:32:16,710 --> 00:32:18,140
[Office of Justice]

762
00:32:24,060 --> 00:32:25,070
No.

